movies.title: D-Day the Sixth of June
movies.plot: En route to Normandy, an American and a British officer reminisce in flashback about their romances with the same woman.

movies.title: Around the World in Eighty Days
movies.plot: Based on the famous book by Jules Verne the movie follows Phileas Fogg on his journey around the world. Which has to be completed within 80 days, a very short period for those days.

events.title: Phileas Fogg leaves London to travel around the world

movies.title: Reach for the Sky
movies.plot: The true story of airman Douglas Bader who overcame the loss of both legs in a 1931 flying accident to become a successful fighter pilot and wing leader during World War II.
movies.awards: Won 1 BAFTA Film Award. Another 4 nominations.

events.title: Douglas Bader is shot down over France and captured
Douglas Bader flies over London to celebrate the anniversary of the Battle of Britain

movies.title: The Captain from Kopenick
movies.plot: The 1956 movie based on the theater play by Carl Zuckmayer based on the true story of cobbler Wilhelm Voigt who dressed up as a German military officer and, with the help of unsuspecting soldiers, took over the city hall in Köpenick and confiscated the city's purse.
movies.awards: Nominated for 1 Oscar. Another 11 wins & 3 nominations.
